      "rationale": "All experimental hemolysis and PIV measurements were conducted in an ISO 17025-accredited laboratory. Flow rates controlled to ±0.5% of set point via calibrated Coriolis meters (NIST-traceable calibration certificates on file). Rotational speed held to ±10 RPM via closed-loop encoder feedback. Blood analog fluid (porcine blood, hematocrit 35±1%, verified by Coulter counter before and after each run) and temperature maintained at 37.0±0.2°C. Measurement uncertainty budgets documented per GUM:2008 for all test parameters and propagated into UQ framework."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-mae-below-20pct-relative",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison performed using mean absolute error (MAE), relative error, and u-pooled metric (ASME V&V 20). MAE = 0.0021 g/100L against experimental mean NIH = 0.018 g/100L (11.7% relative error). The u-pooled comparison metric E/u_val = 0.73 < 1.0 at all 5 operating points, confirming predictions are statistically consistent with measurements. Velocity field NRMS error 4.2% across 1,847 PIV locations. All comparisons documented in ValidationResult vr-hemolysis-absolute-5op and vr-velocity-piv with full uncertainty propagation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
