      "rationale": "Iterative solver convergence assessed at every time step. Velocity and pressure residuals reduced to < 1e-8 (normalized L2 norm) before advancing; hemolysis scalar transport residuals < 1e-10. Round-off error assessed by running double-precision and quad-precision variants on a representative operating point; NIH difference < 0.01%. Linear solver (GAMG with GaussSeidel smoother) convergence history archived for all 5 operating points. No solver divergence or stagnation events observed across the full Monte Carlo ensemble of 10,000 samples."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-independent-review-checklist",
      "rationale": "An independent simulation analyst (not involved in model development) reproduced all 5 operating-point simulations from the archived input files following a documented simulation execution procedure (SEP-COU2-v2). Results matched original predictions to within 0.02% for NIH, confirming reproducibility. A formal use-error checklist covering boundary condition assignment, mesh import, material property specification, solver settings, and post-processing scripts was completed and signed off by a senior reviewer. All deviations from the SEP were documented; none affected QoI by more than 0.1%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-uncertainty-quantified-sobol",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty addressed at three levels. (1) Turbulence model: SST k-omega selected based on comparative study against k-epsilon, RSM, and LES on the FDA nozzle benchmark; SST k-omega produced lowest NIH prediction error (8.3% vs. 14.1% for k-epsilon). (2) Hemolysis model: power-law Giersiepen-Wurzinger coefficients C and alpha treated as uncertain parameters in Monte Carlo UQ with literature-derived distributions; Sobol first-order index S1(C)=0.29 confirms sensitivity is captured. (3) Non-Newtonian blood rheology: Carreau-Yasuda model benchmarked against Newtonian assumption; NIH difference < 3% at VAD operating conditions, within UQ bounds. Model form uncertainty contribution documented and bounded."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-uq-8params-monte-carlo-n10000",
      "rationale": "Eight uncertain input parameters identified via expert elicitation and literature review: blood viscosity (CV 4%), pump clearance gap (±25 μm uniform), inlet hematocrit (35±1% normal), rotational speed tolerance (±10 RPM uniform), power-law coefficient C (log-normal, μ=3.62e-7, σ=0.18 decades), power-law exponent alpha (normal, μ=2.416, σ=0.08), inlet velocity profile shape parameter (±5% turbulence intensity), and outlet pressure (±50 Pa uniform). Monte Carlo ensemble of 10,000 Latin hypercube samples propagated through the full CFD model using a validated surrogate (Gaussian process, LOO-CV R²=0.998). 95% CI on NIH at worst-case operating point: [0.014, 0.023] g/100L, fully below 0.1 g/100L threshold."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
