      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis measurements performed with n=6 independent biological replicates (6 separate porcine blood preparations) at each of the 5 operating points (30 total measurements). Statistical power analysis (80% power, alpha=0.05, two-sided t-test against threshold) confirmed n=6 is sufficient to detect a 15% difference from the clinical threshold. Coefficient of variation across replicates ranged from 4.1% to 7.8%, consistent with published inter-laboratory variability for NIH measurements. Sample traceability (donor ID, preparation date, hematocrit, storage conditions) documented in laboratory notebook LN-2025-FDA-PUMP-001."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/input-equivalency-simulation-vs-experiment-matched",
      "rationale": "A parameter-by-parameter equivalency matrix was constructed comparing simulation inputs to experimental conditions for all 8 uncertain parameters and all 5 operating points. Flow rates, rotational speeds, fluid properties (viscosity, density, hematocrit), temperature, and geometric dimensions were matched between simulation and experiment to within measurement uncertainty at each operating point. Pump clearance gap measured via coordinate measuring machine (CMM) post-test and incorporated into simulation geometry; deviation from nominal < 18 μm (within the ±25 μm uncertainty band). No systematic offsets between simulation inputs and experimental conditions were identified. Equivalency matrix archived as document EQM-COU2-2025-v1."
